---
layout: base.njk
title: "Wolf Mood Generator"
---
<div id="introText">Your wolf is feeling…</div>
<h2 id="moodName">—</h2>
<ul id="effectsList" class="effects"></ul>

<div class="btn-group">
  <button onclick="generateMood()">
    <img src="/assets/icons/wolfpaw.webp" alt="" class="btn-icon"> New Mood
  </button>
  <button class="secondary" onclick="generateFeralMood()">
    <img src="/assets/icons/skull.webp" alt="" class="btn-icon"> Feral Mood
  </button>
</div>

<div class="notes">
  <strong>Notes</strong>
  <p>
    - You are encouraged to take your wolf’s personality into account — e.g. a cowardly wolf in a “Daring” mood may have a much lower bar for what counts as daring.
  </p>
  <p>
    - 'Feral Moods' are more intense, drastic states — they reflect heightened instinct, not supernatural forces. A wolf in a Frenzied or Haunted mood is simply acting on deep emotion.
  </p>
</div>

<script src="{{ '/scripts/mood-generator.js' | url }}"></script>
